# Database Modification Safety

When asked to modify, delete, or recreate a database file (e.g., `.db`, `.sqlite`, `.sqlite3`), you MUST always create a backup of the database file first.

## Rules
- Before running commands like `rm`, `sqlite3`, or Python scripts that drop/recreate tables on a database file, copy the file to a backup location (e.g., `cp database.db database.db.bak`).
- If the user asks you to "nuke", "reset", or "clear" the database, still create a backup first unless they explicitly say "do not back it up".
- Inform the user that you have created a backup and where it is located.

## Example

```bash
# ❌ BAD
rm -f ~/.slurm-ci/slurm_ci.db

# ✅ GOOD
cp ~/.slurm-ci/slurm_ci.db ~/.slurm-ci/slurm_ci.db.bak
rm -f ~/.slurm-ci/slurm_ci.db
```
